TRANSFER IN vs TRANSFER OUT — both must work:

TRANSFER OUT (user is sender):
- Header icon: arrow-up-right, red background
- Header title: "Transfer sent"
- Amount: "−0.2000 CC" in red
- From: user's own address (highlight as "You")
- To: receiver address

TRANSFER IN (user is receiver):
- Header icon: arrow-down-left, green background  
- Header title: "Transfer received"
- Amount: "+0.2000 CC" in green
- From: sender address
- To: user's own address (highlight as "You")

Detection logic (already in inferOnChainType):
- If sender_address === user partyId → TRANSFER_OUT
- If receiver_address === user partyId → TRANSFER_IN

For the "You" highlight:
- When showing user's own address in From or To field,
  append " (You)" label in muted text
- Compare against partyId passed to the component

Make sure the modal receives partyId so it can 
determine which address is "You":
Pass partyId prop to TransactionDetailModal 
and through to TransactionDetailContent.